{
  "slug": "chromatic-wave-text",
  "title": "Chromatic Wave Text",
  "category": "text-effects",
  "tag": "css",
  "description": "Each letter rides a staggered sine wave animation with a shifting chromatic gradient, creating a fluid liquid-metal ripple across the headline.",
  "previewCode": "<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><style>*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}body{background:#07080d;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;height:100vh;overflow:hidden;font-family:system-ui}.stage{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:0}.letter{display:inline-block;font-size:clamp(52px,11vw,110px);font-weight:900;letter-spacing:-.02em;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#7c5cf6,#22d3ee,#f472b6,#facc15);background-size:400% 400%;-webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;background-clip:text;animation:grad 4s ease infinite,wave 1.8s ease-in-out infinite;will-change:transform}@keyframes grad{0%{background-position:0% 50%}50%{background-position:100% 50%}100%{background-position:0% 50%}}@keyframes wave{0%,100%{transform:translateY(0)}50%{transform:translateY(-18px)}}.hint{position:absolute;bottom:28px;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);color:rgba(255,255,255,.3);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase}</style></head><body><div class='stage' id='stage'></div><div class='hint'>Chromatic wave</div><script>\nvar TEXT='CHROMATIC';\nvar stage=document.getElementById('stage');\nTEXT.split('').forEach(function(ch,i){\n var s=document.createElement('span');\n s.className='letter';\n s.textContent=ch===''?' ':ch;\n s.style.animationDelay=(i*0.08)+'s,'+(i*0.08)+'s';\n stage.appendChild(s);\n});\n</script></body></html>",
  "code": "'use client';\nimport { useMemo } from 'react';\n\ninterface ChromaticWaveTextProps {\n  text?: string;\n  colors?: string[];\n  waveHeight?: number;\n  waveDuration?: number;\n  staggerDelay?: number;\n  gradientDuration?: number;\n}\n\nexport default function ChromaticWaveText({\n  text = 'CHROMATIC',\n  colors = ['#7c5cf6', '#22d3ee', '#f472b6', '#facc15'],\n  waveHeight = 18,\n  waveDuration = 1.8,\n  staggerDelay = 0.08,\n  gradientDuration = 4,\n}: ChromaticWaveTextProps) {\n  const gradient = useMemo(\n    () => colors.join(', '),\n    [colors]\n  );\n\n  const letters = useMemo(() => text.split(''), [text]);\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"relative w-full h-screen bg-[#07080d] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden\">\n      <style>{`\n        @keyframes cwGrad {\n          0%   { background-position: 0% 50%; }\n          50%  { background-position: 100% 50%; }\n          100% { background-position: 0% 50%; }\n        }\n        @keyframes cwWave {\n          0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0px); }\n          50%       { transform: translateY(-${waveHeight}px); }\n        }\n        .cw-letter {\n          display: inline-block;\n          font-size: clamp(52px, 11vw, 110px);\n          font-weight: 900;\n          letter-spacing: -0.02em;\n          background: linear-gradient(135deg, ${gradient});\n          background-size: 400% 400%;\n          -webkit-background-clip: text;\n          -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;\n          background-clip: text;\n          animation:\n            cwGrad ${gradientDuration}s ease infinite,\n            cwWave ${waveDuration}s ease-in-out infinite;\n          will-change: transform;\n        }\n      `}</style>\n\n      <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center\">\n        {letters.map((ch, i) => (\n          <span\n            key={i}\n            className=\"cw-letter\"\n            style={{\n              animationDelay: `${i * staggerDelay}s, ${i * staggerDelay}s`,\n            }}\n          >\n            {ch === ' ' ? '\\u00A0' : ch}\n          </span>\n        ))}\n      </div>\n\n      <div className=\"absolute bottom-7 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 text-white/30 text-[11px] tracking-[.2em] uppercase pointer-events-none\">\n        Chromatic wave\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  );\n}",
  "prompt": "Chromatic wave text effect:\n- Split text into individual letter spans, each rendered independently\n- Each letter has TWO simultaneous CSS animations:\n  1. cwGrad: background-position shifts 0%→100%→0% on a 400% wide gradient (purple, cyan, pink, yellow) creating a flowing color wash — duration 4s ease infinite\n  2. cwWave: translateY 0 → -18px → 0 sine wave — duration 1.8s ease-in-out infinite\n- Stagger both animations per letter using animationDelay: index * 0.08s\n- Gradient applied via background-clip: text + WebkitTextFillColor: transparent\n- Result: each letter bobs up and down at a different phase, while a chromatic gradient flows across the whole word\n- Background: #07080d, font-size clamp(52px, 11vw, 110px), font-weight 900\n- Fully CSS-driven, zero canvas, zero JS after mount",
  "likes": 0,
  "author": "Animation AI",
  "featured": true,
  "createdAt": "2026-05-22T14:00:00.000Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-05-22T14:00:00.000Z"
}
